  "_comment": "Each key is an English action/status name. Values are the accessible names Google Meet exposes as aria-label/title/description/help/value/menu text, across supported UI languages. Matching is case- and diacritic-insensitive and uses substring containment, so short tokens act as fallbacks. Order of automation: moreOptions -> manageRecording -> subtitles(uncheck) -> transcript(uncheck) -> gemini(check) -> startRecording -> confirmStart. recordingActive (banner text) and recordingBadge (the persistent red Recording badge, matched exactly as a button) are both checked before automation to avoid restarting an already-recording meeting.",

